

# OVERWATCH  — Full Rescan Analysis & Comprehensive Recommendations

## Architectural Shift Summary

**`app.py` has been decomposed into 14 root-level modules.** What was a ~1,500-line monolith is now:

| Module | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| `shell.py` | Top-level render flow: startup, access checks, sidebar chrome, idle pause, dispatch |
| `navigation.py` | Sidebar section selection, visible sections, transition state |
| `route_registry.py` | Dependency-light canonical routes, aliases, retired-route state |
| `runtime_state.py` | Centralized session-state key constants + `get/set/pop_state` |
| `section_dispatch.py` | Lazy section loading (moved out of `sections/__init__.py`) |
| `access_control.py` | Role capture, admin gating, Snowflake availability probing |
| `filters.py`, `layout.py`, `refresh.py` | Global command bar, chrome, refresh contracts |
| `perf_trace.py`, `performance.py`, `app_entry_timing.py` | Phase tracing, query budgets, entry timing |
| `version.py`, `workflow_contracts.py` | Version metadata, workflow contracts |

Other changes: nav regrouped to **MONITORING CORE / FINANCIAL CONTROL / OPERATIONS / SECURITY** (6 sections); `sections/dba_control_room/` is now a **package** (`__init__.py` + `render.py`); new `sections/base.py` (canonical `LazyPandas`/`lazy_util`), `utils/primitives.py` (dependency-light converters), `sections/triage_queue.py` (Mission Control queue built only from loaded session evidence); `pyproject.toml` added to artifacts; app repositioned as an **admin-only production monitoring app** (`ADMIN_ACCESS_ROLES`, `BUILD_LABEL = "Production monitoring app"`).

