## What Was Fixed ✅

- **✅ Lazy-isolation breaks in shells** — the offending shells (`workload_operations_shell`, `governance_security`, `alert_center_shell`) were removed entirely; routes now point at the workhorse modules, and `section_dispatch.py` preserves lazy loading. `sections/base.py` gives every section one canonical lazy-import toolkit.
- **✅ `build_executive_command_board_sql` confirmed** at line 854 of `command_board.py` — the flagged export exists.
- **✅ Nav/registry drift protection** — `assert tuple(PRIMARY_SECTIONS) == _ROUTE_PRIMARY_SECTION_TITLES` fails fast at startup if config drifts from `route_registry.py`. Exactly the kind of guard this codebase needed.
- **✅ `SECTION_WORKSPACE_STATE_KEYS` duplication** — replaced by `SECTION_ROUTE_STATE` in `route_registry.py`, a single source of truth for per-route session-state seeding.
- **✅ `runtime_state.py`** — state keys as named constants eliminates the magic-string sprawl flagged repeatedly.
- **✅ `utils/primitives.py`** — canonical `safe_float`/`safe_int`, ending the private `_safe_float` duplication across shells.
- **✅ `DEFAULT_ALERT_EMAILS`** remains a single corporate address with a governance comment. No regression.
- **✅ `snowflake.yml`** manifest updated with all 14 root modules — no missing-artifact deploy risk.

